text: The following is a partial list of the "A" codes for Medical Subject Headings (MeSH), as defined by the United States National Library of Medicine (NLM). This list continues the information at List of MeSH codes (A03). Codes following these are found at List of MeSH codes (A05). For other MeSH codes, see List of MeSH codes. Authoritative sources for this content are the MeSH Browser and MeSH SPARQL Explorer. == – respiratory system== === – larynx=== * – glottis * – vocal cords * – laryngeal cartilages * – arytenoid cartilage * – cricoid cartilage * – epiglottis * – thyroid cartilage * – laryngeal mucosa * – goblet cells * – laryngeal muscles === – lung=== * – bronchi * - bronchioles * – pulmonary alveoli * - alveolar epithelial cells * – blood-air barrier === – nose=== * – nasal bone * - nasal cartilage * – nasal cavity * – nasal mucosa * – goblet cells * – olfactory mucosa * – olfactory receptor neurons * – nasal septum * – vomeronasal organ * – paranasal sinuses * – ethmoid sinus * – frontal sinus * – maxillary sinus * – sphenoid sinus * – turbinates === – pharynx=== * – hypopharynx * - pyriform sinus * – nasopharynx * - adenoid * – oropharynx * – tonsil * – pharyngeal muscles * – esophageal sphincter, upper * - velopharyngeal port === – pleura=== === – respiratory mucosa=== * – goblet cells * – laryngeal mucosa * – nasal mucosa * – olfactory mucosa * – olfactory receptor neurons === – trachea=== ==Notes== A04
